**Todo App REST API**

This API will manage tasks, users, and user tasks. The API will have the following endpoints:

### Users Endpoints

#### GET /users
Returns all users.

```bash
GET /users
```

#### POST /users
Creates a new user.

```bash
POST /users
  -name: string
  -email: string
```

### Tasks Endpoints

#### GET /tasks
Returns all tasks for the logged-in user.

```bash
GET /tasks
```

#### GET /tasks/{id}
Returns task details by ID.

```bash
GET /tasks/{id}
  -task_id: integer
```

#### POST /tasks
Creates a new task for the logged-in user.

```bash
POST /tasks
  -title: string
  -description: string
```

#### PUT /tasks/{id}
Updates an existing task by ID.

```bash
PUT /tasks/{id}
  -task_id: integer
  -title: string
  -description: string
```

#### DELETE /tasks/{id}
Deletes a task by ID.

```bash
DELETE /tasks/{id}
  -task_id: integer
```

### Authentication Endpoints

#### Login
Logs in the user with email and password.

```bash
POST /login
  -email: string
  -password: string
```

#### Logout
Logs out the current user.

```bash
DELETE /logout
```

### Example Use Cases

1. Creating a new user:

   ```bash
POST /users
  -name: John Doe
  -email: johndoe@example.com
  -password: password123
```

2. Creating a new task:

   ```bash
POST /tasks
  -title: Buy milk
  -description: Milk is needed for breakfast.
```

3. Updating an existing task:

   ```bash
PUT /tasks/1
  -task_id: 1
  -title: Buy eggs
  -description: Eggs are also needed for breakfast.
```

4. Deleting a task:

   ```bash
DELETE /tasks/1
  -task_id: 1
```

### Implementation

The API will be implemented using Node.js and Express.js.

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const mongoose = require('mongoose');

// Connect to MongoDB
mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost/todo-app', { useNewUrlParser: true, useUnifiedTopology: true });

// Define user model
const User = mongoose.model('User', {
  name: String,
  email: String,
});

// Define task model
const Task = mongoose.model('Task', {
  title: String,
  description: String,
});

// Login endpoint
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  const { email, password } = req.body;
  // Check if user exists and password matches
  User.findOne({ email }, (err, user) => {
    if (err || !user) return res.status(401).send('Invalid credentials');
    if (user.password !== password) return res.status(401).send('Invalid password');
    req.session.user = user;
    res.send('Logged in successfully');
  });
});

// Logout endpoint
app.delete('/logout', (req, res) => {
  req.session.destroy((err) => {
    if (err) console.error(err);
    else res.send('Logged out successfully');
  });
});

// Get all tasks for logged-in user
app.get('/tasks', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
  const tasks = await Task.find().populate('user');
  res.json(tasks);
});

// Create new task for logged-in user
app.post('/tasks', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
  const { title, description } = req.body;
  const task = await Task.create({ title, description, user: req.user._id });
  res.json(task);
});

// Update existing task
app.put('/tasks/:id', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id;
  const { title, description } = req.body;
  const task = await Task.findById(id).populate('user');
  if (!task) return res.status(404).send('Task not found');
  task.title = title;
  task.description = description;
  await task.save();
  res.json(task);
});

// Delete existing task
app.delete('/tasks/:id', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id;
  const task = await Task.findById(id).populate('user');
  if (!task) return res.status(404).send('Task not found');
  await task.remove();
  res.send('Task deleted successfully');
});

